Requirments:
To run, this implimentation requires all default packages in python 3.6 (lower versions will not work, this implimentation
uses the 'secrets' library that was introduced in python 3.6


Usages:
Base arguments
usage: main.py [-h] [--cmdtext] text {encrypt,decrypt} ...

positional arguments:
  text               The plaintext wanted to be encrypted/decrypted, by default assumed to be a filename which will be read in
  {encrypt,decrypt}  Option to specify to encrypt or decrypt the input
    encrypt          Option to select to encrypt input
    decrypt          Option to select to decrypt input

optional arguments:
  -h, --help         show this help message and exit
  --cmdtext          Specify this argument if the text entered on the
                     commandline is the text to operate on, it is by default
                     treated as a filename

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Encryption operation usage
usage: main.py text encrypt [-h] [--blocksize {32,64,128}] [--keysize KEYSIZE]
                            [--rounds ROUNDS] outfile

positional arguments:
  outfile               Name of output encrypted file

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --blocksize {32,64,128}
                        The block size in bits for the cipher to operate on
                        the input data (32, 64, 128), default is 64
  --keysize KEYSIZE     The key size in bits for the cihper to generate
                        (0-2040), default is 128
  --rounds ROUNDS       The number of rounds used in the key expansion (0-255), default is 12

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Decryption operation usage
usage: main.py text decrypt [-h] key outfile

positional arguments:
  key         The .key file generated by the encryption operation
  outfile     Name of output unencrypted file

optional arguments:
  -h, --help  show this help message and exit
  
References:
Algorithm primarily implimented from description on https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RC5
  
  
  
